article.description: Keith Braxton had career-highs of 17 points, 12 rebounds, and five assists to help St. Francis (PA) cruise to an 87-72 victory over Longwood on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Braxton scores 17 points; St. Francis (PA) beats Longwood
article.linkText: Braxton scores 17 points; St. Francis (PA) beats Longwood
article.story: LORETTO, Pa. -- Keith Braxton had career-highs of 17 points, 12 rebounds, and five assists to help St. Francis (PA) cruise to an 87-72 victory over Longwood on Wednesday night. Josh Nebo scored 15 points, and Jamaal King added 15 points and a career-best nine assists for St. Francis (2-2), which shot 60 percent on 36-of-60 shooting. Randall Gaskins Jr. had 11 points. Darrion Allen had 21 points, including 5 of 9 from 3-point range to lead Longwood (1-3). Khris Lane chipped in 17 points and four 3-pointers. JaShaun Smith had 14 points. The Red Flash used a 20-2 run over a six-minute span to close the first half with a 42-25 halftime lead. St. Francis had a 21-point lead five minutes into the second half and cruised from there. It was the first meeting between the schools.
